nt  home  pegasus investing in sustainability  wellness we are a private alternative asset management firm providing strategic growth capital to middlemarket companies focused on sustainability and wellness sectors learn more passion for investing and a better tomorrow pegasus is comprised of a diverse team of investment professionals and advisors who leverage the intellectual capital of the firm to unlock the intrinsic value within our investments b under management  investment professionals  advisors  private equity funds  private equity transactions newsroom s setting a new standard in consumer and clinical sleep technology news article july   spend it better how tech is improving  things taking up your time news article july   odes to joy an uplifting return to the seychelles news article july   s setting a new standard in consumer and clinical sleep technology news article july   spend it better how tech is improving  things taking up your time news article july   odes to joy an uplifting return to the seychelles news article july   view more our locations headquarters connecticut  river road cos cob ct  new york  third ave new york ny  pegasus capital advisors  wikipedia pegasus capital advisors from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from pegasus capital jump to navigation search pegasus capital advisors lp type partnership industry private equity founded  headquarters new york new york united states key people craig cogut managing partner products leveraged buyout growth capital total assets  billion number of employees  website wwwpcalpcom pegasus capital advisors lp is a private equity investment firm founded in  by former cofounder of apollo management and drexel burnham lambert lawyer craig cogut who has been its managing partner pegasus specializes in sourcing buying and building middlemarket companies that compete on the basis of sustainability and resource efficiency the firm has raised four funds since inception and currentlywhen manages us billion in capital its offices are located in new york city ny and cos cob ct they have made over  investments in various companies such as igps lighting science molycorp minerals universal lubricants and cannondalecitation needed in  the firm was appointed by governor arnold schwarzenegger of california as financial advisor to the r regions of climate action to facilitate develop and implement lowcarbon and climate resilient projects contents  history  funds  portfolio  competitors  references  external links historyedit history of private equity and venture capital early history origins of modern private equity the s leveraged buyout boom the s leveraged buyout and the venture capital bubble the s dotcom bubble to the credit crunch v t e pegasus was founded by craig cogut in   years after dealing with virtually all aspects of distressed securities investments and restructurings of apollo management which he and leon black and craig cogut started at former investment banking power drexel burnham lambert when that bank was besieged by allegations over illegal activities involving highyield debt cogut established pegasus to focus on investments in middlemarket companies facing financial distress where returns from deals are more reliant on the actual alpha of the investorcitation needed cogut wanted to concentrate on transactions that could generate returns through revenue growth and operating improvements rather than largely relying on financial leveragecitation needed in october  governor arnold schwarzenegger of california appointed the firm as financial advisor to the r regions of climate action to facilitate and implement lowcarbon and climate resilient projects fundsedit since  pegasus has raised five private equity funds with total investor commitments of c  billiondead link pegasus raises the capital from a variety of limited partners that include major public and corporate pension funds leading endowments fund of funds and family offices it closed its fourth private equity fund in january  hitting the us million cap that had been set and its fifth fund in april dead link pegasus partners i    millioncitation needed pegasus partners ii    million pegasus partners iii    million pegasus partners iv    million pegasus partners v    millioncitation needed as of december   funds ii iii iv and v achieved returns of    and  respectively portfolioedit since  pegasus has invested in more than  companiescitation needed the firm tends to invest in the consumer products technology business services energy financial services industrial manufacturing and communications sectorscitation needed selected companies of the firms investments arecitation needed universal lubricants molycorp minerals lighting science igps traxys cannondale bicycle corporation jenzabar psi carols daughter imagesat international nsi spirit music group tm protection resources hain pure protein corporation competitorsedit pegasus competes with other major private equity players in the middlemarket including kohlberg  company audax group berkshire partners golden gate capital and madison dearborn partnerscitation needed referencesedit  a b executive profile craig m cogut bloomberg businessweek february     r governance official website of the r  october    about pegasus capital advisors section httpsfinanceyahoocomnewspegasuscapitaladvisorsprnewshtml  httpwwwprivateequitywirecoukarticlesdetailjspcontentid  a b c pegasus partners iv closes on m altassets december    colorado pera alternative investments portfolio  auction finds buyer for bicycle maker new york times march   external linksedit companies portal pegasus capital advisors lp company website v t e private equity and venture capital investment firms investment strategy venture growth mezzanine secondaries leveraged buyout history history of private equity and venture capital early history of private equity private equity in the s private equity in the s private equity in the s investors angel investor c