bert lawyer craig cogut who has been its managing partner pegasus specializes in sourcing buying and building middlemarket companies that compete on the basis of sustainability and resource efficiency the firm has raised four funds since inception and currentlywhen manages us billion in capital its offices are located in new york city ny and cos cob ct they have made over  investments in various companies such as igps lighting science molycorp minerals universal lubricants and cannondalecitation needed in  the firm was appointed by governor arnold schwarzenegger of california as financial advisor to the r regions of climate action to facilitate develop and implement lowcarbon and climate resilient projects contents  history  funds  portfolio  competitors  references  external links historyedit history of private equity and venture capital early history origins of modern private equity the s leveraged buyout boom the s leveraged buyout and the venture capital bubble the s dotcom bubble to the credit crunch v t e pegasus was founded by craig cogut in   years after dealing with virtually all aspects of distressed securities investments and restructurings of apollo management which he and leon black and craig cogut started at former investment banking power drexel burnham lambert when that bank was besieged by allegations over illegal activities involving highyield debt cogut established pegasus to focus on investments in middlemarket companies facing financial distress where returns from deals are more reliant on the actual alpha of the investorcitation needed cogut wanted to concentrate on transactions that could generate returns through revenue growth and operating improvements rather than largely relying on financial leveragecitation needed in october  governor arnold schwarzenegger of california appointed the firm as financial advisor to the r regions of climate action to facilitate and implement lowcarbon and climate resilient projects fundsedit since  pegasus has raised five private equity funds with total investor commitments of c  billiondead link pegasus raises the capital from a variety of limited partners that include major public and corporate pension funds leading endowments fund of funds and family offices it closed its fourth private equity fund in january  hitting the us million cap that had been set and its fifth fund in april dead link pegasus partners i    millioncitation needed pegasus partners ii    million pegasus partners iii    million pegasus partners iv    million pegasus partners v    millioncitation needed as of december   funds ii iii iv and v achieved returns of    and  respectively portfolioedit since  pegasus has invested in more than  companiescitation needed the firm tends to invest in the consumer products technology business services energy financial services industrial manufacturing and communications sectorscitation needed selected companies of the firms investments arecitation needed universal lubricants molycorp minerals lighting science igps traxys cannondale bicycle corporation jenzabar psi carols daughter imagesat international nsi spirit music group tm protection resources hain pure protein corporation competitorsedit pegasus competes with other major private equity players in the middlemarket including kohlberg  company audax group berkshire partners golden gate capital and madison dearborn partnerscitation needed referencesedit  a b executive profile craig m cogut bloomberg businessweek february     r governance official website of the r  october    about pegasus capital advisors section httpsfinanceyahoocomnewspegasuscapitaladvisorsprnewshtml  httpwwwprivateequitywirecoukarticlesdetailjspcontentid  a b c pegasus partners iv closes on m altassets december    colorado pera alternative investments portfolio  auction finds buyer for bicycle maker new york times march   external linksedit companies portal pegasus capital advisors lp company website v t e private equity and venture capital